WEBVTT

01:00.327 --> 01:01.393
[FELIX] Hey, uh...

01:06.534 --> 01:08.500
It's all right.

01:09.470 --> 01:11.470
[BIRDS CHIRPING IN THE DISTANCE]

01:11.472 --> 01:12.738
Yeah, I think so.

01:14.075 --> 01:16.075
I really screwed up.

01:17.578 --> 01:19.111
Yes, it is.

01:21.148 --> 01:23.782
I never expected any of this.

01:27.354 --> 01:28.620
I would...

01:34.095 --> 01:35.828
I crossed the line.

01:45.439 --> 01:50.442
["JUST PRETENDING" BY
THE VERSATILES PLAYS]

02:22.610 --> 02:24.510
[CUTLERY CLANGS GLASS]

02:26.547 --> 02:28.147
[HILLARY] Felix,
without you, this company

02:28.149 --> 02:30.549
would not be what it is today.

02:30.551 --> 02:32.518
My father loved
working with you,

02:32.520 --> 02:35.554
just as I know
you loved working with him.

02:35.556 --> 02:38.891
This has been difficult
for us all.

02:38.893 --> 02:41.160
We're really going
to miss you around here.

02:41.162 --> 02:43.562
Oh, that face.

02:43.564 --> 02:45.164
Your energy.

02:45.166 --> 02:46.732
Expertise.

02:46.734 --> 02:49.601
But I do know that Anne,
your beautiful wife...

02:49.603 --> 02:51.570
I'm sure she's just going
to be delighted

02:51.572 --> 02:52.804
to have you all to herself.

02:52.806 --> 02:55.507
So, to Felix.

02:56.577 --> 02:59.945
May the next chapter
treat you well.

03:02.716 --> 03:04.483
[WOMAN] I'm so happy for you.

03:04.485 --> 03:06.318
Thank you.

03:08.889 --> 03:10.656
I know Dan couldn't
be here today.

03:10.658 --> 03:12.624
He's off golfing or traipsing
around the world

03:12.626 --> 03:17.196
or living the life
that he so richly deserves.

03:17.198 --> 03:19.264
But he was my mentor.

03:20.601 --> 03:22.734
I owe him everything.

03:22.736 --> 03:25.571
It's been an honor to work
with you all, to know you,

03:25.573 --> 03:27.673
to learn from you.

03:27.675 --> 03:29.875
And, Hillary,

03:29.877 --> 03:33.745
I only hope that you can
maintain the integrity

03:33.747 --> 03:37.583
and the innovation that is
the cornerstone of this firm.

03:38.719 --> 03:40.953
However, I want you all to know

03:40.955 --> 03:44.990
that I am not going gently
into this good light.

03:44.992 --> 03:49.328
On the contrary,
this is merely a transition.

03:50.764 --> 03:52.831
I encourage you all to...

03:54.868 --> 03:58.003
to call me
if you need any help...

03:59.873 --> 04:01.573
or if I can be of any service.

04:01.575 --> 04:02.774
- Thanks. Thank you.
- [APPLAUSE]

04:02.776 --> 04:04.543
[HILLARY] Felix, before you go.

04:04.545 --> 04:06.712
We got you a little
parting gift.

04:06.714 --> 04:08.547
- How'd you get those?
- Well, it wasn't easy.

04:08.549 --> 04:09.881
- It wasn't cheap.
- Wow.

04:09.883 --> 04:11.550
Open it.

04:11.552 --> 04:12.951
[FELIX] Okay.

04:12.953 --> 04:14.753
[HILLARY] We didn't want you
getting lonely

04:14.755 --> 04:16.922
with all your newfound
free time.

04:16.923 --> 04:18.923
[FELIX] What?

04:18.926 --> 04:20.325
It's a buddy for you.

04:20.327 --> 04:21.726
It's not a buddy.

04:21.728 --> 04:22.961
It's an augmented
reality companion.

04:22.963 --> 04:25.297
Companion. Assistant. Whatever.

04:25.299 --> 04:26.698
Thank you.

04:26.700 --> 04:28.033
[WOMAN] Go ahead, try it on.

04:28.035 --> 04:31.303
No, I've got to pack up.

04:31.305 --> 04:33.805
It's my daughter's birthday
tonight, so...

04:33.807 --> 04:35.007
thanks.

04:35.009 --> 04:36.675
Thank you all. Thanks.

04:36.677 --> 04:38.577
- Thanks, Felix.
- Thank you, Felix.

04:38.579 --> 04:40.379
Happy birthday to Grace.

04:43.584 --> 04:45.550
[GRACE] How was the party, Dad?

04:45.552 --> 04:47.286
It wasn't really a party.
More of just a lunch.

04:47.288 --> 04:48.654
But it was fine. It was good.

04:48.656 --> 04:50.355
What did Dan say?

04:50.357 --> 04:52.624
Dan wasn't there.
It was just Hillary.

04:52.626 --> 04:54.359
- That little shit.
- Honey.

04:54.361 --> 04:56.061
[ANNE] I want to see the watch.

04:56.063 --> 04:58.397
You know what?
They didn't give me a watch.

04:59.033 --> 05:00.699
They gave me something else.

05:00.701 --> 05:02.701
But they said
it was very expensive.

05:02.703 --> 05:04.970
Well, must be nice knowing
you get to live

05:04.972 --> 05:06.638
in your sweatpants from now on.

05:06.640 --> 05:08.040
Don't put me out to pasture
just yet.

05:08.042 --> 05:09.574
[LAUGHS]

05:09.576 --> 05:11.009
I'm delighted for you, honey.

05:11.011 --> 05:12.878
I'm a little jealous,
but I am delighted.

05:12.880 --> 05:14.946
Oh, you can wear your
sweatpants to work anytime.

05:14.948 --> 05:16.648
Yeah, sure. Why not?

05:18.385 --> 05:21.086
So do you have big birthday
plans with your friends?

05:21.088 --> 05:23.088
Uh, Ben's taking me out
for sushi tomorrow night

05:23.090 --> 05:25.324
and we're going to meet up
with Eve and her boyfriends.

05:25.326 --> 05:27.592
[ANNE] Oh, Eve. How is she?

05:27.594 --> 05:30.028
- Who?
- [ANNE] You met her.

05:30.030 --> 05:33.832
I can't keep them straight,
I swear.

05:33.834 --> 05:35.000
How is everything with Ben?

05:35.002 --> 05:36.735
[GRACE] Good.

05:36.737 --> 05:38.737
Great, actually.

05:38.739 --> 05:39.971
[ANNE] Everything okay?

05:40.874 --> 05:42.040
[GRACE] Yeah.

05:42.042 --> 05:45.844
Uh... [ANNE] What's up?

05:47.014 --> 05:49.748
Okay, it's not a big deal.

05:52.386 --> 05:53.752
Grace?

05:54.688 --> 05:56.088
Okay.

05:56.090 --> 05:57.856
- Ben and I...
- Oh, my God, you're pregnant.

05:57.858 --> 05:59.758
[GRACE] What? No! Oh, my God!

05:59.760 --> 06:01.626
[FELIX] Would you let her
answer, please?

06:01.628 --> 06:03.428
No. No.

06:03.430 --> 06:07.866
Uh, we have been thinking
about moving in together.

06:07.868 --> 06:09.735
What?

06:09.737 --> 06:11.636
Oh.

06:11.638 --> 06:12.804
That's it.

06:13.841 --> 06:17.376
Well, it seems... fast.

06:17.378 --> 06:19.444
- [GRACE] Mom.
- What?

06:19.446 --> 06:21.780
[ANNE] You've only been seeing
each other for a few months.

06:21.782 --> 06:24.750
I know, but we're...
[ANNE] Felix?

06:26.019 --> 06:27.953
I think it's great.

06:27.955 --> 06:29.121
[GRACE] You do? Really?

06:29.123 --> 06:30.722
What the hell?

06:30.724 --> 06:32.090
You're old enough. You'll learn.

06:33.894 --> 06:35.727
[ANNE] You feel ready?

06:37.030 --> 06:39.064
Yeah. Yeah, I do.

06:39.066 --> 06:40.866
Okay.

06:41.869 --> 06:43.168
Wow.

06:44.405 --> 06:45.804
Also, we already found a place

06:45.806 --> 06:47.005
and put down a deposit, so...

06:49.042 --> 06:51.042
Okay.

06:51.044 --> 06:53.812
- [ANNE] Look at you.
- [GRACE] Oh, my God.

06:53.814 --> 06:54.980
[ANNE SIGHS]

06:54.982 --> 06:56.715
[FELIX] You were a beauty.

06:56.717 --> 06:58.750
Wait, that was still
your first place, right?

06:58.752 --> 07:00.986
That's right, and your father
and I dated for two whole years

07:00.988 --> 07:02.721
before we moved in together.

07:02.723 --> 07:04.089
- [GRACE] Oh, my God.
- [FELIX] All right!

07:04.091 --> 07:06.091
Way to make a point.
Good for you, honey.

07:06.093 --> 07:08.026
Hey, that's what I could do.

07:08.028 --> 07:09.828
I could be a birthday clown now.

07:09.830 --> 07:11.163
[LAUGHS]

07:13.967 --> 07:15.901
[ANNE] Well, she seems happy.

07:15.903 --> 07:17.202
Yup.

07:18.839 --> 07:20.705
It's a big day for you.

07:20.707 --> 07:21.873
Yes, it is.

07:21.875 --> 07:23.542
How are you feeling?

07:24.978 --> 07:26.211
Oh, I don't know.

07:26.213 --> 07:28.780
You know, yes,
it's great for us.

07:28.782 --> 07:30.816
- Yeah.
- Sure.

07:31.919 --> 07:33.885
Felix, I know that
you felt pushed out,

07:33.887 --> 07:36.455
but I do think
that this could be

07:36.457 --> 07:38.523
very good for you and for us.

07:38.525 --> 07:39.958
Okay.

07:40.861 --> 07:41.993
You coming up?

07:41.995 --> 07:44.129
- Soon.
- Okay.

07:44.131 --> 07:45.964
I just want to
finish some emails.

07:45.966 --> 07:48.099
All right.
I'll see you up there.

07:48.101 --> 07:49.868
Okay.

07:49.870 --> 07:51.069
I love you.

07:51.071 --> 07:52.737
Hey.

07:52.739 --> 07:54.072
Congratulations.

07:54.074 --> 07:57.476
- [IMITATING GUNS FIRING]
- [LAUGHS]

08:08.155 --> 08:09.754
[COMPUTER, FEMALE VOICE]
Welcome to Auggie,

08:09.756 --> 08:11.223
where seeing is believing.

08:11.225 --> 08:15.093
And we believe in a future
together, not alone.

08:15.095 --> 08:19.130
Be it an executive assistant
or personal companion,

08:19.132 --> 08:20.899
Auggie determines your needs

08:20.901 --> 08:23.101
by reading your
subconscious brain signals

08:23.103 --> 08:26.972
via sensors consolidated
into the arms of the glasses.

08:26.974 --> 08:30.775
A microprocessor integrated
into the bridge of the frame

08:30.777 --> 08:34.513
projects the desired companion
onto the user's environment.

08:34.515 --> 08:38.116
Simply put the glasses on
and say hello.

08:43.890 --> 08:45.524
[ANNE] And the fridge
is pretty much empty,

08:45.526 --> 08:47.926
so if you wouldn't mind
running to the store?

08:49.530 --> 08:51.596
Felix?

08:51.598 --> 08:53.031
Okay.

08:55.569 --> 08:58.870
[ANNE] All right. I love you.

08:58.872 --> 09:00.805
And I love you.

09:00.807 --> 09:02.974
- Enjoy today.
- Yeah.

09:04.244 --> 09:05.944
Yeah, maybe I'll write a novel.

09:05.946 --> 09:07.546
[ANNE LAUGHS]

10:31.164 --> 10:32.664
[P.A. SYSTEM BEEPS]

10:32.666 --> 10:34.299
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER SPEAKERS]

10:39.172 --> 10:43.074
Come on, you know I can't.

10:43.076 --> 10:46.044
Well, I mean,
it is my favorite flavor.

10:46.046 --> 10:49.347
No. You know I need
to watch my intake.

10:49.349 --> 10:51.349
[LAUGHING] Stop it.

10:51.351 --> 10:53.251
Oh, God, yes.

10:53.253 --> 10:54.919
I know I deserve it.

10:54.921 --> 10:56.988
[LAUGHING] The new me.

10:56.990 --> 11:00.659
You really think I deserve
chocolate chips and nibs?

11:00.661 --> 11:02.661
[LAUGHS]

11:02.663 --> 11:04.996
You are too much!

11:04.998 --> 11:06.164
Okay.

11:06.166 --> 11:08.133
[LAUGHING] Oh, God!

11:09.202 --> 11:12.704
Oh, you are just over the top.

11:48.308 --> 11:50.141
[AUGGIE] Felix?

11:57.250 --> 11:59.017
Hey, there.

11:59.019 --> 12:01.252
It's okay.
I know this is strange.

12:02.422 --> 12:04.489
- Yeah, I'm sorry.
- [AUGGIE] Don't be.

12:05.992 --> 12:10.095
I... I wasn't expecting this.

12:10.097 --> 12:12.063
[AUGGIE] Why?

12:12.065 --> 12:13.465
[LAUGHS]

12:13.467 --> 12:15.233
You're so pretty.

12:15.235 --> 12:17.135
[AUGGIE CHUCKLES]

12:17.137 --> 12:18.803
I'm sorry, what do I call you?

12:18.805 --> 12:20.305
[AUGGIE] I'm Auggie.

12:20.307 --> 12:22.173
Of course you are.

12:22.175 --> 12:23.775
Um...

12:24.344 --> 12:26.144
Nice to meet you?

12:27.414 --> 12:29.114
Likewise.

12:31.051 --> 12:33.218
[CHUCKLES] You're staring.

12:33.220 --> 12:35.286
[FELIX] Yeah, I'm sorry.

12:35.288 --> 12:37.856
- [CELL PHONE VIBRATES]
- Oh, excuse me.

12:40.761 --> 12:42.193
Hey.

12:42.195 --> 12:43.762
[ANNE] Hey, did you go
to the store yet?

12:43.764 --> 12:45.463
- Yeah.
- [ANNE] Oh.

12:45.465 --> 12:47.232
I forgot to mention
we needed detergent.

12:47.234 --> 12:49.134
You didn't pick up any, did you?

12:49.136 --> 12:51.035
- I didn't, no. I'm sorry.
- [ANNE] No, it's okay.

12:51.037 --> 12:52.170
I'll just grab it
on the way home.

12:52.172 --> 12:53.438
Okay.

12:53.440 --> 12:55.073
All right,
I'll talk to you later?

12:55.075 --> 12:56.755
- [ANNE] All right, bye.
- Okay. Yeah, bye.

13:08.855 --> 13:10.855
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]
- [KEYPAD BEEPS]

13:22.803 --> 13:25.537
[JACK] So if you accept
it would mean longer hours,

13:25.539 --> 13:28.072
but, of course,
a significant pay increase.

13:28.074 --> 13:30.141
More control over operations,

13:30.143 --> 13:32.877
final approval on pitches,
et cetera.

13:32.879 --> 13:34.479
I feel like I'm leaving
something out.

13:34.481 --> 13:38.316
Oh, and it would also mean
more contact with me.

13:38.318 --> 13:40.084
- Unfortunately.
- [BOTH LAUGH]

13:40.086 --> 13:41.352
Joy.

13:41.354 --> 13:43.354
I know, and that's awful,
but, uh...

13:43.356 --> 13:45.857
so, what do you think?

13:46.593 --> 13:48.560
[EXHALES]

14:01.842 --> 14:03.875
[DOOR OPENS]

14:03.877 --> 14:05.243
[ANNE] Hey!

14:05.245 --> 14:06.544
- [DOOR CLOSES]
- [FELIX] Oh, hey.

14:06.546 --> 14:09.447
Honey, you're here.

14:12.118 --> 14:14.385
[POP MUSIC PLAYING FAINTLY]

14:16.156 --> 14:18.122
- You tired?
- Hmm?

14:18.124 --> 14:19.457
You seem tired.

14:19.459 --> 14:21.259
Yeah. I'm tired.

14:21.261 --> 14:23.127
I'm sorry.

14:23.129 --> 14:24.629
Oh, did you see the pictures
that Grace sent us?

14:24.631 --> 14:26.598
Oh, not yet.

14:33.607 --> 14:35.907
Oh, honey...

14:35.909 --> 14:38.476
I got to tell you
about this story

14:38.478 --> 14:41.512
about this lady I saw
in the grocery store today.

14:41.514 --> 14:43.147
So she's standing in the aisle,

14:43.149 --> 14:44.482
and she was wearing
these glasses.

14:44.484 --> 14:46.517
- Mm-hmm?
- Hon, I got this.

14:46.519 --> 14:48.253
And it was funny,

14:48.255 --> 14:49.554
because they were
the same glasses

14:49.556 --> 14:50.655
that the company gave me.

14:50.657 --> 14:52.290
- So...
- Mm. Felix?

14:52.292 --> 14:53.892
I'm so exhausted.

14:53.894 --> 14:55.994
Can you tell me about this
in the morning?

14:57.264 --> 14:58.897
- Yeah, of course.
- I'm sorry, honey.

14:58.899 --> 15:01.199
- It's okay.
- Mmm.

15:01.201 --> 15:04.202
Will you be very quiet
when you come upstairs?

15:04.204 --> 15:05.670
Yeah.

15:43.576 --> 15:45.209
Hey.

15:45.211 --> 15:46.678
How was your day?

15:48.715 --> 15:50.481
It was fine.

15:50.483 --> 15:52.417
Just fine?

15:53.353 --> 15:54.619
Well, it was kind of slow.

15:54.621 --> 15:58.022
I'm transitioning
professionally.

15:58.024 --> 16:00.024
Out of architecture.

16:00.026 --> 16:02.293
Yeah, how'd you know that?

16:04.597 --> 16:07.298
I know everything
about you, Felix.

16:09.336 --> 16:10.568
[LAUGHS]

16:10.570 --> 16:12.704
Relax, I'm... I'm just kidding.

16:12.706 --> 16:14.439
Well, kind of.

16:15.375 --> 16:17.041
So you're in my head?

16:17.043 --> 16:18.710
Correct.

16:20.013 --> 16:22.313
And you know everything
I'm thinking?

16:22.315 --> 16:23.681
Unfortunately.

16:26.019 --> 16:28.252
And the way you look?

16:28.254 --> 16:29.988
You're not happy
with the way I look?

16:29.990 --> 16:31.422
No.

16:31.424 --> 16:33.458
No, on the contrary, I...

16:34.394 --> 16:35.660
You're beautiful.

16:37.263 --> 16:38.763
Can I make you look
any way I want?

16:38.765 --> 16:41.666
Like, can you be a man,
or ugly, or something?

16:41.668 --> 16:43.434
No.

16:45.305 --> 16:47.605
So you look like this
to everybody?

16:48.541 --> 16:50.541
No. Just for you.

16:51.678 --> 16:53.678
Well, that's kind of creepy.

16:53.680 --> 16:56.481
There's nothing creepy about it.

17:01.087 --> 17:03.421
So today I'm in
this grocery store.

17:03.423 --> 17:05.323
I see this woman
cracking up, okay?

17:05.325 --> 17:07.025
Talking to herself.

17:07.027 --> 17:09.327
But I guess she wasn't
talking to herself.

17:09.329 --> 17:11.561
Oh, yeah? What happened?

17:13.066 --> 17:14.632
Well, she was wearing
these Auggie glasses.

17:14.634 --> 17:18.435
So, you know,
she's talking to her Auggie.

17:18.438 --> 17:19.771
Cool.

17:19.772 --> 17:21.606
Yeah, cool.

17:22.575 --> 17:24.108
And, uh...

17:26.311 --> 17:27.712
she seemed happy.

17:27.714 --> 17:32.050
But from my vantage point,
it was sort of sad.

17:32.052 --> 17:34.385
You know, she seemed
very solitary.

17:36.589 --> 17:38.523
But was she?

17:40.460 --> 17:42.493
I guess she wasn't.

17:42.495 --> 17:44.195
[AUGGIE] Are you?

17:45.498 --> 17:47.131
No.

17:48.401 --> 17:50.068
[AUGGIE] Good.

17:51.371 --> 17:52.737
Yeah.

17:55.108 --> 17:57.608
Ah, Jesus. Look at the time.

17:57.610 --> 17:59.343
[AUGGIE]
Yeah, way past your bedtime.

17:59.345 --> 18:02.080
Yeah, it is. I'm sorry.
I have to go up.

18:02.082 --> 18:04.115
Good night, Felix.

18:05.351 --> 18:06.818
Good night.

18:13.093 --> 18:15.493
[BIRDS TWEETING]

18:17.497 --> 18:18.729
[ANNE] How'd you sleep?

18:18.731 --> 18:20.164
Pretty great.

18:20.166 --> 18:21.566
[ANNE]
What time did you come up?

18:21.568 --> 18:22.834
I didn't even hear you.

18:22.836 --> 18:25.169
Well, honey, you asked me
to be quiet.

18:28.441 --> 18:30.108
You know, Felix,

18:30.110 --> 18:33.711
I know that this retirement
thing was unexpected,

18:33.713 --> 18:36.848
and it certainly can't be easy.

18:36.850 --> 18:39.784
But I just keep thinking
about all the times

18:39.786 --> 18:43.187
you have talked about
wanting to do some consulting.

18:43.189 --> 18:45.756
I know. I know.
I've been thinking about it too.

18:45.758 --> 18:47.725
I mean, hell, it's...

18:47.727 --> 18:49.727
It's really what I've been
doing the past couple of years.

18:49.729 --> 18:51.629
- Right?
- I need to start all over again.

18:51.631 --> 18:53.197
- Oh, Jesus.
- No, no. I know.

18:53.199 --> 18:55.666
But, I think about
all your connections

18:55.668 --> 18:57.135
and your body of work.

18:57.137 --> 18:59.904
And, Felix, to be your own boss?

18:59.906 --> 19:01.606
I know.

19:01.608 --> 19:02.807
- [CELL PHONE VIBRATES]
- All right.

19:02.809 --> 19:04.208
I'll put out some feelers.

19:04.210 --> 19:05.510
I'll make some calls.

19:05.512 --> 19:06.878
I love it. Sorry.

19:08.481 --> 19:10.214
Hey, what's up?

19:12.418 --> 19:13.618
[SIGHS]

19:13.620 --> 19:16.888
I... not yet, but I will.

19:18.925 --> 19:21.759
That is... Thank you, Jack.

19:24.564 --> 19:26.531
No, but I'm on my way in.

19:26.533 --> 19:29.233
Mm-hmm. All right. I'm on it.

19:29.235 --> 19:31.836
I'll see you soon. Okay, bye.

19:31.838 --> 19:33.171
You okay?

19:33.173 --> 19:35.640
- Yeah.
- What's up?

19:39.179 --> 19:40.912
A position has opened up,

19:40.914 --> 19:43.648
and Jack has asked me
to fill it.

19:44.884 --> 19:46.584
Oh.

19:46.586 --> 19:49.453
It's the Executive
VP of Marketing.

19:49.455 --> 19:51.455
Wow.

19:51.457 --> 19:53.524
But I didn't want to accept
until you and I had a chance

19:53.526 --> 19:54.892
to talk about it.

19:57.463 --> 19:59.830
All right, well, we're talking.
A lot more money?

19:59.832 --> 20:01.699
[SIGHS] It's more money.

20:01.701 --> 20:03.868
It's more hours.
It would be more responsibility.

20:03.870 --> 20:06.771
But I'll tell you,
it's one of those things.

20:06.773 --> 20:10.875
I didn't know that I wanted it
until it was offered to me.

20:13.546 --> 20:15.479
Well, that's great.

20:15.481 --> 20:17.215
- Really?
- Yeah.

20:17.217 --> 20:20.251
You work hard. You deserve it.
You'd be great at it.

20:20.253 --> 20:22.853
I just think it could be
perfect for us right now.

20:22.855 --> 20:27.592
I do think it would be
a bit of an adjustment, but...

20:27.594 --> 20:29.527
I think it's wonderful.
Congratulations.

20:29.529 --> 20:30.995
Thank you, Felix.

20:30.997 --> 20:33.831
- Yeah.
- Now I really do have to go.

20:34.968 --> 20:36.567
Mwah.

20:36.569 --> 20:37.868
I love you.

20:37.870 --> 20:39.770
And I love you.

22:01.621 --> 22:03.020
[SEAGULL SQUAWKS]

22:08.961 --> 22:10.695
Good morning.

22:10.697 --> 22:12.029
Hey.

22:14.767 --> 22:17.435
It's so beautiful.

22:18.638 --> 22:19.970
Isn't it?

22:21.741 --> 22:23.874
It's one of my favorite places.

22:24.977 --> 22:26.811
Come here all the time.

22:28.715 --> 22:30.948
I wanted you to see it.

22:32.852 --> 22:34.452
I appreciate it.

22:37.023 --> 22:39.357
Shall we?

22:39.359 --> 22:40.758
[LAUGHS]

22:40.760 --> 22:42.093
I got it.

22:48.835 --> 22:50.968
[GIGGLES] Come on.

23:06.085 --> 23:08.386
[AUGGIE] It's so quiet.

23:09.956 --> 23:11.655
Thank you.

23:11.657 --> 23:13.057
[FELIX] For what?

23:13.059 --> 23:15.092
Bringing me here.

23:18.931 --> 23:20.881
I love it here.

23:20.882 --> 23:22.832
I just come out alone,
and I sit and ruminate.

23:22.835 --> 23:25.836
Just get a lot of my ideas here.

23:27.673 --> 23:29.807
I haven't brought anybody here
in ages.

23:31.043 --> 23:33.511
What about Anne?

23:34.881 --> 23:36.814
Well...

23:36.816 --> 23:39.450
We don't have to talk about her
if you don't want to.

23:42.755 --> 23:46.157
It's just, I'm getting used
to how this thing works.

24:05.511 --> 24:07.445
[KNOCK ON WINDOW]

24:10.116 --> 24:12.583
- [DOOR OPENS]
- [DOOR CHIME JINGLES]

24:14.854 --> 24:16.220
Honey, I'm sorry I'm late.

24:16.222 --> 24:19.490
Stop it. It's okay. Hi.
Where were you?

24:20.860 --> 24:22.860
I had a meeting with Hillary.

24:22.862 --> 24:26.063
Oh. Well, thank God you never
have to deal with her again.

24:26.065 --> 24:28.966
[LAUGHS] Ay... Chihuahua.

24:28.968 --> 24:30.868
[GRACE LAUGHS]

24:30.870 --> 24:35.206
Well, you could have texted me,
but I forgive you.

24:35.208 --> 24:36.941
[WAITER] Can I get you
anything to drink?

24:36.943 --> 24:38.209
[FELIX]
I'm fine with water, thank you.

24:38.211 --> 24:39.977
[WAITER] You got it.

24:39.979 --> 24:41.178
So, what was it about?

24:41.180 --> 24:42.813
What?

24:42.815 --> 24:44.748
Uh, the meeting?

24:44.750 --> 24:48.519
Oh, I'm just tying up
some loose ends at the office.

24:49.889 --> 24:51.889
Uh, Mom told me
about her promotion.

24:51.891 --> 24:53.123
- I know.
- Whoa.

24:53.125 --> 24:54.859
- Pretty great.
- Yeah.

24:54.861 --> 24:57.161
She seems really on edge

24:57.163 --> 25:00.164
about me and Ben
moving in together.

25:00.166 --> 25:01.799
Honey, she loves you.

25:01.801 --> 25:03.033
She's concerned.

25:03.035 --> 25:04.835
- I... Yeah.
- Let her be a mother.

25:04.837 --> 25:07.171
- You're right.
- Oh, speaking of which.

25:08.774 --> 25:10.274
- That's a gift.
- What is this?

25:10.276 --> 25:12.243
- Just open it.
- Oh, my God, Dad!

25:12.245 --> 25:14.245
Stop it. That's so sweet.

25:14.247 --> 25:16.046
- I know.
- Thank you.

25:16.048 --> 25:17.882
Wow. I was... I was adorable.

25:17.884 --> 25:19.517
- Yes, you were.
- I was undeniably adorable.

25:19.519 --> 25:21.285
[GRACE LAUGHS]

25:21.287 --> 25:23.587
You're going to do
just great there.

25:28.895 --> 25:30.294
[MAN 1, ON TV]
Look at that, Larry.

25:30.296 --> 25:32.129
- [MAN 2, ON TV] Where?
- [MAN 1] In the sky.

25:32.131 --> 25:33.998
- [MAN 2] What? The stars?
- [MAN 1] No, Larry, the moon.

25:34.000 --> 25:35.833
[TURNS TV OFF]

25:35.835 --> 25:37.868
[IMITATING JAMES STEWART]
You want the moon, Auggie?

25:37.870 --> 25:40.538
I'll lasso it for you.

25:40.540 --> 25:42.139
Hey.

25:42.141 --> 25:44.241
[LAUGHS]

25:44.243 --> 25:46.544
You want to join me?

25:46.546 --> 25:48.312
Sure.

25:51.817 --> 25:53.083
Oh.

25:54.954 --> 25:56.287
What?

26:00.960 --> 26:02.626
Nothing.

26:04.964 --> 26:07.565
What do you want to do tomorrow?

26:07.567 --> 26:09.900
I don't know.

26:09.902 --> 26:11.902
Where's your creativity?

26:12.271 --> 26:14.138
Good question.

26:14.140 --> 26:16.106
I guess you're retired.
Life's over.

26:16.108 --> 26:17.641
You know, you might as well die.

26:18.844 --> 26:20.177
All right.

26:20.179 --> 26:22.580
You've got a lot more to offer.

26:22.582 --> 26:24.615
Yeah, sure.

26:25.585 --> 26:26.984
Life's short.

26:26.986 --> 26:28.285
Don't waste it.

26:34.594 --> 26:36.093
[CREAKING]

26:36.095 --> 26:38.262
Oh. Hey, I'm sorry, I...

26:38.264 --> 26:40.097
I must have fallen asleep.

26:40.099 --> 26:42.299
[ANNE, WHISPERING]
Shh. Go back to sleep.

26:42.301 --> 26:45.002
Okay, I will. Sorry.

26:45.004 --> 26:46.170
Good night.

26:50.610 --> 26:52.242
[DOOR CLOSES]

26:58.017 --> 26:59.950
[MUFFLED DIALOGUE]

27:04.256 --> 27:06.190
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

27:15.701 --> 27:18.068
[INAUDIBLE]

27:37.923 --> 27:39.723
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

27:41.060 --> 27:43.961
[ANNE] Wow! What is all this?

27:43.963 --> 27:45.195
I hope you're hungry.

27:45.197 --> 27:46.997
I'm starving.

27:46.999 --> 27:48.198
Sit down.

27:49.335 --> 27:51.301
- How was your day?
- It was great.

27:51.303 --> 27:54.672
We finalized this pitch that
we've been struggling with.

27:54.674 --> 27:56.707
- Congratulations. That's great.
- Well, thank you.

27:56.709 --> 27:58.676
What are we celebrating?

27:58.678 --> 28:02.012
Well, I spoke to Graciella.
She liked the presentation.

28:02.014 --> 28:05.049
And she said that
she's willing to partner

28:05.051 --> 28:07.384
if I can raise the bulk
of the initial capital.

28:07.386 --> 28:09.319
Wow.

28:09.321 --> 28:10.988
So, what are we talking about?

28:10.990 --> 28:13.390
Would that come out
of our savings?

28:13.392 --> 28:15.025
I don't know.

28:15.027 --> 28:16.360
Just asking.

28:16.362 --> 28:18.128
What are you
bringing that up for, huh?

28:18.130 --> 28:20.030
Let's not focus
on the obstacles, okay?

28:20.032 --> 28:21.699
Felix, I'm just
asking questions.

28:21.701 --> 28:24.201
I just thought that you
would be excited for me.

28:24.203 --> 28:25.769
Jesus, Anne.

28:27.173 --> 28:29.206
[WINE POURING]

28:35.981 --> 28:37.715
[AUGGIE] You okay?

28:39.251 --> 28:41.185
I don't know.

28:41.187 --> 28:43.754
I'm just looking for a reason
to wake up in the morning.

28:43.756 --> 28:45.322
I mean, is it me?
Am I being unreasonable?

28:45.324 --> 28:47.024
I don't think so.

28:47.026 --> 28:48.425
No.

28:48.427 --> 28:51.128
I thought this
is what she wanted.

28:51.130 --> 28:55.799
I mean, for Christ's sake,
she initiated it.

28:57.169 --> 29:00.137
It's hard to know exactly
what other people want.

29:00.139 --> 29:01.338
Uh-huh.

29:01.340 --> 29:03.307
What do you want?

29:04.143 --> 29:05.809
I don't know.

29:05.811 --> 29:07.244
Lots of things.

29:09.014 --> 29:10.147
Come on.

29:11.350 --> 29:13.016
Get up, Felix.

29:13.018 --> 29:15.152
I want to show you something.

29:16.055 --> 29:18.088
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]

29:24.430 --> 29:26.497
[INHALES AND EXHALES DEEPLY]

29:43.449 --> 29:46.350
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER]
You asked. We delivered.

29:46.352 --> 29:48.352
Intimacy on demand.

29:48.354 --> 29:51.088
Introducing Auggie Touch.

29:51.090 --> 29:52.456
Order yours today.

29:52.458 --> 29:54.925
Rush delivery available.

29:57.062 --> 29:58.862
Is this what you want?

30:00.065 --> 30:01.532
I-I-I don't know.

30:04.236 --> 30:07.337
Yeah, in part, okay.

30:07.339 --> 30:09.339
You seem unsure.

30:09.341 --> 30:11.175
[LAUGHS] You think?

30:11.177 --> 30:12.543
Is it Anne?

30:14.480 --> 30:16.547
What?

30:16.549 --> 30:19.950
I don't know whether
I want to do this. I mean...

30:21.353 --> 30:23.420
Is this what you want?

30:25.224 --> 30:26.824
Yes.

30:36.869 --> 30:39.369
- [ANNE] Felix?
- Hey.

30:39.371 --> 30:40.604
What's up?

30:40.606 --> 30:42.840
[INHALES AND EXHALES]

30:42.842 --> 30:46.510
I would love to hear more
about the partnership.

30:46.512 --> 30:48.512
Okay, fine.

30:49.548 --> 30:51.481
Can I take a look?

30:51.483 --> 30:54.284
There's not much
to see right now.

30:54.286 --> 30:57.454
But you already sent
your presentation over, right?

30:57.456 --> 30:59.256
It's just another draft.

30:59.258 --> 31:01.191
Well, I would love to see it.

31:02.361 --> 31:04.595
Okay. Yeah, fine. Hold on. Yeah.

31:12.538 --> 31:14.905
I think it looks great.

31:14.907 --> 31:16.607
Thank you.

31:16.609 --> 31:19.543
And let's...
let's talk about the money.

31:19.545 --> 31:21.411
I'm sure that we can
figure something out.

31:21.413 --> 31:23.480
Honey, it's fine. I swear.

31:23.482 --> 31:25.215
Okay?

31:28.354 --> 31:29.887
I'll see you upstairs.

31:29.889 --> 31:31.288
Okay.

31:47.539 --> 31:51.909
[ANNE] I think Kosha and I are going
to go back to their place later on.

31:51.911 --> 31:54.244
Maybe you and Jim
could have a guy's night.

31:54.246 --> 31:56.313
Felix?

31:56.315 --> 31:57.581
[FELIX] Uh-huh?

31:57.583 --> 31:59.917
[ANNE]
I know he's not your favorite,

31:59.919 --> 32:02.953
but it might be good
to make more of an effort.

32:02.955 --> 32:05.188
[FELIX] Yeah. Maybe.

32:05.190 --> 32:06.523
[ANNE]
I just mean outside of work.

32:06.525 --> 32:09.192
You should be enjoying yourself.

32:09.194 --> 32:11.261
[FELIX] Yeah, yeah.

32:14.633 --> 32:16.700
What are you doing?

32:16.702 --> 32:18.969
You know what? You go in.

32:18.971 --> 32:20.437
What are you talking about?

32:20.439 --> 32:22.339
Kosha was looking forward
to seeing you.

32:22.341 --> 32:23.941
I know. I'm not feeling so hot.

32:23.943 --> 32:25.409
Are you okay?

32:25.411 --> 32:28.545
Yeah. I have a bug or something.

32:29.615 --> 32:31.281
Okay.

32:32.217 --> 32:33.650
Okay. Go. You have fun.

32:35.220 --> 32:37.220
I love you.

32:37.222 --> 32:38.588
Yeah, I love you too.

32:46.999 --> 32:49.533
[FELIX CHUCKLING]

32:49.535 --> 32:51.535
[FELIX]
You don't get cold, do you?

32:53.572 --> 32:55.305
Oh, pardon me.

32:56.508 --> 32:58.542
[INAUDIBLE]

32:58.544 --> 33:00.043
That's a pretty jacket.

33:04.550 --> 33:06.049
[LAUGHS] Wow.

33:10.389 --> 33:11.655
Felix!

33:11.657 --> 33:13.991
- Hiya, Jim.
- Hey, buddy.

33:13.993 --> 33:15.459
I almost didn't recognize you.

33:15.461 --> 33:17.995
When'd you, uh,
start wearing glasses?

33:17.997 --> 33:20.630
Oh... They come with age.
You'll find out.

33:20.632 --> 33:22.532
Of course, of course.
You look great.

33:22.534 --> 33:24.434
- Oh, thank you.
- So you keeping busy?

33:24.436 --> 33:28.271
Yeah. Yeah, you know,
I'm doing some consulting work.

33:28.273 --> 33:30.007
- That's perfect for you.
- It's going well, yeah.

33:30.009 --> 33:31.475
So, listen.
I've got to get going.

33:31.477 --> 33:34.544
Okay. Okay. Oh, hey,
let's get together soon.

33:34.546 --> 33:36.346
The girls and I will do dinner...

33:36.348 --> 33:38.448
I think that's great.
You got it. It's a date.

33:38.450 --> 33:40.717
All right. Take... Take care.

33:45.524 --> 33:47.424
[PLAYING HORN]

34:42.147 --> 34:44.347
[KOSHA] So, wait,
tell me more about this promotion.

34:44.349 --> 34:46.483
Tell me everything.

34:46.485 --> 34:48.085
Well, I totally
wasn't expecting it.

34:48.087 --> 34:50.120
They offered it to me
out of nowhere.

34:50.121 --> 34:51.487
They?

34:51.489 --> 34:53.757
- Jack.
- Ah-ha.

34:53.759 --> 34:55.092
Your little work crush.

34:55.094 --> 34:57.527
- Easy. Easy.
- [LAUGHS]

34:57.529 --> 34:59.663
No. Timing's a little tough,
though.

34:59.665 --> 35:02.499
- Why?
- Mm, Felix.

35:02.501 --> 35:05.569
But he has been working
on his consulting business,

35:05.571 --> 35:07.137
which is great.

35:07.139 --> 35:10.407
But we've both been so busy.
We just...

35:10.409 --> 35:13.477
We haven't had the time
to get on the same page.

35:13.479 --> 35:14.845
- You know?
- Yeah, I bet.

35:14.847 --> 35:16.413
You know how he can be.

35:16.415 --> 35:17.781
But I am proud of him

35:17.783 --> 35:20.884
that he picked himself up
during a time like this.

35:20.886 --> 35:22.652
I don't know.

35:23.889 --> 35:27.224
He seems like he's been
a little... off.

35:28.427 --> 35:29.793
Hmm.

35:31.663 --> 35:32.896
Jim said he saw him
downtown today.

35:32.898 --> 35:34.865
He said he seemed really happy.

35:34.867 --> 35:37.267
- Not today.
- Yeah.

35:56.188 --> 35:57.621
Keeping up?

35:57.623 --> 35:59.156
Yes, I am.

36:00.425 --> 36:02.225
Keep going. Just up ahead.

36:14.873 --> 36:17.307
[FELIX] Isn't it beautiful, huh?

36:21.180 --> 36:22.779
Wow.

36:25.784 --> 36:27.884
I'm coming. I'm coming.
Don't worry.

36:27.886 --> 36:29.719
You be careful.

36:32.691 --> 36:34.291
Wow.

36:35.594 --> 36:36.893
Look at you.

36:40.732 --> 36:44.267
We're almost there.
It's just over the bridge.

36:59.685 --> 37:01.551
Is it worth it?

37:02.621 --> 37:03.954
Yes.

37:44.963 --> 37:46.730
I just...

37:49.601 --> 37:51.001
I know.

38:22.334 --> 38:24.634
[BEEPING]

38:24.636 --> 38:26.336
[EXHALES]

38:47.059 --> 38:49.326
[TAP WATER RUNNING]

41:28.153 --> 41:30.553
[CHUCKLES] Oh, Jesus.

42:11.162 --> 42:12.629
Hi.

43:28.273 --> 43:30.206
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]

43:44.889 --> 43:46.623
Hello?

43:46.625 --> 43:48.057
[ANNE, ON PHONE] Hey.

43:48.059 --> 43:49.359
Hey.

43:50.929 --> 43:52.629
[ANNE] Did I wake you?

43:52.631 --> 43:55.098
Yeah, I was...

43:56.034 --> 43:57.667
Oh, my God.

43:57.669 --> 43:59.936
I haven't slept past 9:00
in ages.

43:59.938 --> 44:02.071
[ANNE] I know. I'm impressed.

44:02.073 --> 44:04.307
[LAUGHS] I know.

44:04.309 --> 44:06.042
What's up?

44:06.044 --> 44:07.710
[ANNE] I thought you
might have been working.

44:07.712 --> 44:09.145
[FELIX] I will be.

44:11.049 --> 44:13.349
What's going on?

44:13.351 --> 44:15.952
Uh, I just wanted you to know

44:15.954 --> 44:17.720
that I'm going straight
to McNamara's after work.

44:17.722 --> 44:19.288
They pushed a meeting,
so I won't be able

44:19.290 --> 44:21.190
to come home first.

44:21.192 --> 44:23.192
[FELIX] What time are we
meeting Grace and Ben there?

44:23.194 --> 44:24.694
Seven.

44:24.696 --> 44:26.129
[FELIX]
All right, I'll see you then.

44:26.131 --> 44:27.964
- Okay.
- Bye-bye.

44:27.966 --> 44:29.265
Bye.

44:30.101 --> 44:31.434
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

44:31.436 --> 44:33.202
[JACK]
Hey. Did you see Diane's email?

44:33.204 --> 44:34.937
Yes. Pushed to 5:30.

44:34.939 --> 44:36.939
Right. Also, I was thinking
sushi today,

44:36.941 --> 44:38.274
if you still want to get lunch.

44:38.276 --> 44:39.942
I'm buying.
We could eat in my office?

44:39.944 --> 44:41.778
- That sounds good.
- Perfect.

44:50.355 --> 44:52.288
I know you're watching me.

44:54.092 --> 44:55.692
[FELIX] I can't help it.

44:55.694 --> 44:57.193
[CHUCKLES]

45:01.700 --> 45:03.099
[LAUGHS]

45:13.978 --> 45:15.178
What are you doing?

45:16.214 --> 45:17.780
[AUGGIE GIGGLES]

45:32.997 --> 45:34.464
[AUGGIE] What?

45:37.302 --> 45:39.102
You.

45:39.104 --> 45:40.403
Me?

45:41.473 --> 45:44.440
You're just so... Incredible?

45:44.442 --> 45:46.342
[LAUGHS]

45:47.812 --> 45:49.879
I had no idea.

45:54.185 --> 45:55.818
You okay?

45:58.022 --> 45:59.122
Yeah.

45:59.124 --> 46:01.424
Yeah, I'm just, uh...

46:01.426 --> 46:02.859
I don't know, I'm scared.

46:04.796 --> 46:07.396
[AUGGIE] You're discovering something
you didn't know about yourself

46:07.398 --> 46:10.533
and now you're realizing it.

46:12.303 --> 46:14.804
I'm scared of losing
what I have.

46:16.040 --> 46:18.174
But now I realize
I don't have to.

46:18.176 --> 46:20.443
You have a new perspective.

46:20.445 --> 46:22.211
I do.

46:22.213 --> 46:25.548
When I'm with you,
I see things differently.

46:25.550 --> 46:27.383
Rose-tinted?

46:29.487 --> 46:31.187
Yes.

46:32.791 --> 46:34.791
And I realize that
the world isn't rose-tinted,

46:34.793 --> 46:38.795
but now I have options.

46:38.797 --> 46:40.296
Right?

46:42.167 --> 46:43.432
Right.

46:54.279 --> 46:56.846
I'm back. Any messages?

46:57.549 --> 46:59.315
Thank you.

46:59.317 --> 47:00.917
Perfect.

47:14.365 --> 47:15.898
Seriously, I mean it.

47:15.900 --> 47:18.868
Having you involved
makes all the difference.

47:18.870 --> 47:20.536
Thank you.

47:20.538 --> 47:22.538
And the transition
just seemed so natural.

47:22.540 --> 47:24.340
- Right?
- I know. It's like...

47:24.342 --> 47:27.276
It's like I barely need you
at all anymore.

47:27.278 --> 47:28.845
No, no, no.
This is a partnership.

47:28.847 --> 47:31.447
We are a winning team,
you and I.

47:31.449 --> 47:34.217
Do you usually wear contacts?

47:34.219 --> 47:36.285
Oh, uh, no. Those...

47:36.287 --> 47:37.854
Those are Auggie glasses.

47:37.856 --> 47:39.288
I don't know what that is.

47:39.290 --> 47:41.357
Really? Uh, well,
they're interesting.

47:41.359 --> 47:43.226
Not for everyone.

47:43.228 --> 47:46.863
Um... Why don't you try them on?

47:46.865 --> 47:48.297
Okay.

47:56.875 --> 47:58.641
- Oh, my God!
- [LAUGHS]

47:58.643 --> 48:01.577
What the hell is that?

48:01.579 --> 48:03.279
[JACK] Oh, not a fan, huh?

48:03.281 --> 48:06.482
[ANNE] No, it's like
there's two of you.

48:08.286 --> 48:10.353
Uh, it's a projection
of a companion.

48:10.355 --> 48:12.154
A friend of mine
let me borrow them.

48:12.156 --> 48:13.656
I'm sorry, I-I-I didn't mean
to freak you out.

48:13.658 --> 48:15.458
No, no, no.
It's okay, it's okay.

48:15.460 --> 48:17.593
It's just so strange.

48:17.595 --> 48:21.264
Do you have little
conversations with yourself?

48:21.266 --> 48:25.902
Actually, uh, it projects what
your subconscious wants to see.

48:28.673 --> 48:30.439
Oh, my God, I'm so embarrassed.

48:30.441 --> 48:32.408
- No. Hey, don't be. It's fine.
- You know what?

48:32.410 --> 48:34.911
I'm going to go back
to my office.

48:34.913 --> 48:36.646
It's okay. I'm going to go.

48:36.648 --> 48:38.581
- Uh, no. I'll get it.
- Excuse me.

48:38.583 --> 48:39.949
Yeah.

48:39.951 --> 48:41.550
[EXHALES]

48:44.322 --> 48:45.922
That's great.

48:48.192 --> 48:49.525
[SIGHS]

49:01.306 --> 49:03.539
[SIGHS]

49:05.944 --> 49:08.010
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

49:15.486 --> 49:17.353
[FELIX] Goddamn it, you idiot.

49:17.355 --> 49:18.554
Shit.

49:24.228 --> 49:25.661
[SHOWER WATER RUNS]

49:26.664 --> 49:28.497
[VIBRATING]

49:32.236 --> 49:33.569
Oh shit.

49:33.571 --> 49:35.404
Shit, shit.

49:37.608 --> 49:39.742
Honey. Honey,
I'm on my way, okay?

49:39.744 --> 49:41.978
Yeah, I overslept. I'm so sorry.

49:41.980 --> 49:43.679
What?

49:43.681 --> 49:45.381
Oh, no.

49:45.383 --> 49:46.649
Oh Christ, how is she?

49:46.651 --> 49:48.451
All right, w-w-where?

49:48.453 --> 49:51.387
Okay, I'm... Oh, goddamn it,
I'm so sorry.

49:51.389 --> 49:52.688
I'll be right there.

49:55.693 --> 49:58.594
Annie, where's Grace?

49:58.596 --> 50:00.062
I'm sorry.

50:00.064 --> 50:02.365
I overslept and my alarm
didn't go off.

50:02.367 --> 50:04.266
- Where's Grace?
- She's with Ben.

50:04.268 --> 50:06.569
- They're running some tests.
- How is she doing?

50:07.572 --> 50:09.472
- Oh, hey, Dad.
- Oh, baby.

50:10.508 --> 50:12.408
- How are you doing?
- Hey.

50:14.278 --> 50:16.379
- How are you?
- [GRACE] We're okay.

50:16.381 --> 50:18.414
He has a slight concussion.
We have to keep an eye on him.

50:18.416 --> 50:20.316
- I just hit my head pretty hard.
- Oh, honey.

50:20.318 --> 50:21.684
No, I'm... It's okay.

50:21.686 --> 50:23.319
Can't say the same
about the car, though.

50:23.321 --> 50:25.521
- Why, what happened?
- We got T-boned.

50:25.523 --> 50:27.023
But really, we're both okay.

50:27.025 --> 50:28.491
[GRACE]
I just feel like I'm in shock.

50:28.493 --> 50:29.759
Okay, I got to go
call my mom back.

50:29.761 --> 50:31.093
She's going insane.

50:31.095 --> 50:32.595
Yeah.

50:32.597 --> 50:34.296
Where were you?

50:34.298 --> 50:37.033
I was just napping,
and I overslept,

50:37.035 --> 50:39.101
and the phone was on silent.

50:39.103 --> 50:41.070
- And I'm sorry.
- [GRACE] It's okay.

50:41.072 --> 50:42.505
[FELIX]
Well, as long as you're okay.

50:42.507 --> 50:44.440
Here, honey,
I'll take care of this.

50:44.442 --> 50:46.175
Thanks, Dad.

50:47.378 --> 50:48.644
Okay.

50:58.523 --> 51:00.189
[SNIFFLES]

51:14.439 --> 51:16.138
[DOOR OPENS]

51:17.842 --> 51:19.542
[DOOR CLOSES]

51:19.544 --> 51:21.143
[FELIX] Honey?

51:35.626 --> 51:37.526
I could have driven them home.

51:37.528 --> 51:39.862
- It's fine.
- I feel terrible.

51:41.699 --> 51:44.166
What do you want me to say?

51:44.168 --> 51:47.503
Nothing. Nothing, I don't know.
Nothing. Nothing.

51:49.574 --> 51:51.240
[EXHALES]

51:55.680 --> 51:59.448
Your hair was wet.

51:59.450 --> 52:01.183
What?

52:02.720 --> 52:05.121
At the clinic,
you had just showered.

52:05.123 --> 52:06.655
I told you, I was getting ready
for dinner.

52:06.657 --> 52:08.757
And the other day? Downtown?

52:08.759 --> 52:09.892
What?

52:12.630 --> 52:14.563
I don't even want to say it.

52:14.565 --> 52:15.898
You're wrong.

52:15.900 --> 52:18.467
- Am I?
- Yes.

52:18.469 --> 52:21.537
What else should I think, Felix?

52:21.539 --> 52:22.838
Just, please tell me outright.

52:22.840 --> 52:24.807
Is there?

52:24.809 --> 52:26.475
What?

52:26.477 --> 52:28.878
- Someone else?
- No!

52:30.681 --> 52:34.550
What else do you want me to say?
I'm... I'm telling you the truth!

52:34.552 --> 52:36.819
I don't know where you're
getting these things from.

52:36.821 --> 52:39.421
Okay. Fine. Sorry.

52:39.423 --> 52:41.857
It's been a long day.
Good night, Felix.

52:55.506 --> 52:57.673
[SHOWER WATER RUNNING]

53:47.792 --> 53:49.925
[BIRDS TWEETING]

53:54.765 --> 53:56.665
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]

54:35.573 --> 54:36.972
[AUGGIE] I'm sorry.

54:36.974 --> 54:39.275
Oh, it's not your fault.

54:39.277 --> 54:41.810
It's partly my fault.

54:42.813 --> 54:44.346
Is she okay?

54:45.783 --> 54:47.650
Yeah, she'll be fine.

54:49.620 --> 54:51.987
She has every reason to be mad.

54:54.058 --> 54:56.892
It's like I can't
do anything right.

54:56.894 --> 54:59.695
You're seeing the world
differently, but that's okay.

54:59.697 --> 55:01.930
We'll figure it out.

55:04.635 --> 55:07.569
Maybe you need a distraction.

55:07.571 --> 55:08.837
A new project.

55:08.839 --> 55:10.039
What do you mean?

55:10.041 --> 55:11.640
Come on.

55:34.865 --> 55:36.465
[SIGHS]

55:39.003 --> 55:41.003
[FELIX] What are you doing?

55:41.005 --> 55:42.938
Surveying.

55:42.940 --> 55:44.907
What?

55:44.909 --> 55:46.775
Okay, grab these chairs
and bring them over here.

55:46.777 --> 55:50.846
We're going to need bedsheets,
pillows, and also...

55:50.848 --> 55:52.681
Oh.

55:53.984 --> 55:55.851
Okay.

56:10.801 --> 56:12.701
[EXHALES]

57:02.420 --> 57:03.886
[INHALES DEEPLY]

57:17.034 --> 57:19.034
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]

57:21.705 --> 57:23.505
[PHONE LINE RINGING]

57:23.507 --> 57:25.707
[FELIX, OVER ANSWERING MACHINE]
Hey, this is Felix.

57:25.709 --> 57:27.843
Please leave me a message.

58:09.487 --> 58:11.887
[FELIX SIGHS]

58:21.165 --> 58:23.232
Oh, my God, I love you.

58:26.971 --> 58:29.104
I love you too.

58:35.145 --> 58:36.778
Oh, my God.

58:36.780 --> 58:38.113
- Honey! Honey! Honey!
- Oh, my God.

58:38.115 --> 58:40.249
- Oh, my God.
- Honey, please. No, no, no.

58:40.251 --> 58:41.984
- Let me explain.
- No, no, Felix.

58:41.986 --> 58:43.886
- I know what this is.
- It's not what you think.

58:43.888 --> 58:45.587
- I swear to God, honey...
- Felix, no! Enough!

58:45.589 --> 58:47.189
Goddamn it!

58:47.191 --> 58:50.926
Honey... I am so stupid.

58:50.928 --> 58:52.294
- Please, I don't...
- You know what?

58:52.296 --> 58:54.229
I hope that this makes you
feel very happy.

58:54.231 --> 58:56.064
Honey? Anne? Anne? Anne?

58:56.066 --> 58:57.266
[DOOR OPENS]

58:59.937 --> 59:01.570
- Anne.
- [DOOR CLOSES]

59:02.540 --> 59:06.074
Anne, just...
Annie, listen to me.

59:07.011 --> 59:09.111
Honey, it's nothing!

59:09.113 --> 59:11.613
I'm telling you, it's nothing!

59:12.816 --> 59:14.149
Listen to me.

59:14.151 --> 59:16.051
Honey, just hear me out
for a minute.

59:16.053 --> 59:17.286
Anne?

59:17.288 --> 59:20.155
Annie, just listen to me
for a second.

59:22.927 --> 59:24.660
Just hear me out.

59:26.196 --> 59:28.697
Who do you see
when you wear them?

59:34.104 --> 59:36.071
[STARTS ENGINE]

59:47.618 --> 59:50.052
[VEHICLE DRIVES AWAY]

59:54.358 --> 59:56.658
[DOOR OPENS]

01:00:31.295 --> 01:00:33.895
Hey, are you okay?

01:00:33.897 --> 01:00:35.897
I don't know.

01:00:35.899 --> 01:00:38.767
We don't have to talk about it
unless you want to.

01:00:40.270 --> 01:00:42.404
I don't know what I want.

01:00:42.406 --> 01:00:44.406
That's okay.

01:00:44.408 --> 01:00:47.209
You know, sometimes it's hard
to make sense of these things.

01:00:48.245 --> 01:00:50.312
How would you know?

01:00:53.050 --> 01:00:54.783
Life isn't easy.

01:00:56.086 --> 01:00:57.419
Is that so?

01:01:00.057 --> 01:01:02.391
Let me ask you something.
Do you feel anything?

01:01:05.396 --> 01:01:07.262
Maybe we should go
for a walk and cool down.

01:01:07.264 --> 01:01:09.931
I told you, I don't...
I don't want to go for a walk.

01:01:09.933 --> 01:01:12.300
- I don't know what I want.
- I understand.

01:01:12.302 --> 01:01:13.735
No, you don't.

01:01:13.737 --> 01:01:15.404
How could you?

01:01:16.674 --> 01:01:20.676
Honest to God,
you're not helping.

01:01:20.678 --> 01:01:22.044
What can I do?

01:01:22.046 --> 01:01:23.311
I don't know.

01:01:23.313 --> 01:01:25.013
Goddamn it.

01:01:37.227 --> 01:01:39.428
[PHONE LINE RINGING]

01:01:48.972 --> 01:01:51.039
[ANNE, ON ANSWERING MACHINE]
Hi, you've reached Anne.

01:01:51.041 --> 01:01:52.374
I'm sorry I missed your call,

01:01:52.376 --> 01:01:54.776
but I will get back to you
as soon as I can.

01:01:54.778 --> 01:01:56.244
[ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS]

01:01:56.246 --> 01:01:57.813
[FELIX] Anne, I...

01:01:58.982 --> 01:02:00.982
I don't know what to say.

01:02:00.984 --> 01:02:02.417
Just, uh...

01:02:02.419 --> 01:02:05.253
Please just call me back, okay?

01:02:05.255 --> 01:02:07.122
I'm...

01:02:08.225 --> 01:02:09.491
Okay, bye-bye.

01:02:09.493 --> 01:02:11.159
[PHONE LINE DISCONNECTS]

01:02:20.771 --> 01:02:22.237
[WHISPERS] Hey.

01:04:59.897 --> 01:05:01.463
[DOOR OPENS]

01:05:04.935 --> 01:05:06.401
Hey.

01:05:07.271 --> 01:05:09.271
Hi.

01:05:09.273 --> 01:05:11.373
How are you doing? How's Ben?

01:05:15.345 --> 01:05:16.912
So...

01:05:18.181 --> 01:05:19.414
Dad?

01:05:20.450 --> 01:05:22.684
Can you stop?

01:05:22.686 --> 01:05:24.486
Talk to me.

01:05:35.399 --> 01:05:37.232
You look like shit.

01:05:37.234 --> 01:05:39.367
Fair enough.

01:05:39.369 --> 01:05:40.635
Mom is really hurt.

01:05:40.637 --> 01:05:43.271
- I know.
- She's staying at Kosha's.

01:05:43.273 --> 01:05:45.206
- Good.
- No. Not good.

01:05:45.208 --> 01:05:47.275
You should go be with her.

01:05:47.277 --> 01:05:49.978
Honey, I don't think she wants
to see me right now.

01:05:49.980 --> 01:05:52.080
Whose fault is that?

01:05:53.317 --> 01:05:54.516
I don't know.

01:05:54.518 --> 01:05:55.951
What do you mean,
you don't know?

01:05:55.953 --> 01:05:57.419
You messed up.

01:05:58.555 --> 01:06:00.522
Look, it's not that simple,
honey.

01:06:00.524 --> 01:06:02.557
I mean, there's...

01:06:02.559 --> 01:06:04.392
I'm going through
something right now.

01:06:04.394 --> 01:06:06.394
Yeah, you're sneaking around
like a fucking creep.

01:06:06.396 --> 01:06:09.064
- All right, that's enough.
- No, it's true.

01:06:10.233 --> 01:06:12.667
You have no idea what it's like.

01:06:12.669 --> 01:06:15.370
You wake up in the morning
and nothing.

01:06:15.372 --> 01:06:17.305
You don't need me.

01:06:17.307 --> 01:06:18.573
Your mother doesn't need me.

01:06:18.575 --> 01:06:20.642
And work?

01:06:20.644 --> 01:06:22.577
I'm nothing.

01:06:25.015 --> 01:06:27.349
I used to have value. I-I was...

01:06:28.585 --> 01:06:30.552
I had purpose.

01:06:30.554 --> 01:06:32.721
Now I don't know
what to do with myself, huh?

01:06:32.723 --> 01:06:35.023
So... So, what do I do?
You tell me.

01:06:35.025 --> 01:06:36.992
What about when you showed up

01:06:36.994 --> 01:06:39.527
an hour after Mom
at the hospital?

01:06:40.764 --> 01:06:43.465
- What about it?
- You were taking a nap?

01:06:44.334 --> 01:06:46.601
- I was.
- Stop lying.

01:06:50.741 --> 01:06:53.074
You are so selfish.

01:06:55.512 --> 01:06:57.078
Maybe I am.

01:07:01.651 --> 01:07:04.719
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

01:07:57.407 --> 01:07:58.740
- Hey.
- [FELIX] Hey.

01:07:58.742 --> 01:08:01.076
I'm sorry about earlier.

01:08:04.414 --> 01:08:05.680
It's all right.

01:08:06.750 --> 01:08:09.084
Is Grace going to be okay?

01:08:11.755 --> 01:08:13.488
Yeah, I think so.

01:08:14.524 --> 01:08:16.424
I really screwed up.

01:08:16.426 --> 01:08:17.826
That's not true.

01:08:17.828 --> 01:08:19.527
Yes, it is.

01:08:19.529 --> 01:08:21.629
Nobody is perfect.

01:08:23.500 --> 01:08:25.399
I never expected any of this.

01:08:25.402 --> 01:08:26.634
Me neither.

01:08:26.636 --> 01:08:29.571
But it'll work itself out.

01:08:30.774 --> 01:08:32.707
I crossed the line.

01:08:32.709 --> 01:08:35.143
They'll forgive you.

01:08:36.645 --> 01:08:38.212
I wouldn't.

01:08:39.783 --> 01:08:42.817
And I got to tell you,
I really miss Anne.

01:08:42.819 --> 01:08:44.586
[ANNE] Hey.

01:08:45.755 --> 01:08:48.256
- Hold on, what is...?
- You can apologize to me.

01:08:50.393 --> 01:08:51.725
Anne?

01:08:51.728 --> 01:08:54.595
I know that you're confused.

01:08:54.598 --> 01:08:58.533
But you know that I love you
and Grace loves you.

01:08:58.535 --> 01:09:00.734
You're a good man, Felix.

01:09:00.737 --> 01:09:02.403
You're doing your best.

01:09:02.404 --> 01:09:04.839
We all make mistakes.

01:09:04.841 --> 01:09:07.809
I'm sorry that I've been
pushing you away.

01:09:07.810 --> 01:09:11.613
Oh, God, I'm supposed
to be apologizing to you.

01:09:11.615 --> 01:09:12.814
[LAUGHS]

01:09:12.816 --> 01:09:14.515
I'm sorry.

01:09:14.518 --> 01:09:16.651
I'm here for you.

01:09:19.589 --> 01:09:20.921
[AUGGIE] We both are.

01:09:25.694 --> 01:09:27.629
No, you're not.

01:09:32.769 --> 01:09:34.269
Felix?

01:09:40.243 --> 01:09:42.676
[SEAGULLS SQUAWKING]

01:09:54.925 --> 01:09:56.958
[ANNE, OVER ANSWERING MACHINE]
Hi, you've reached Anne.

01:09:56.960 --> 01:09:59.460
I'm sorry I missed your call,
but I will get back to you

01:09:59.462 --> 01:10:01.262
as soon as I can.

01:10:43.673 --> 01:10:45.673
[SNIFFLES]

01:11:38.962 --> 01:11:41.796
[INHALES DEEPLY AND SIGHS]

01:11:49.005 --> 01:11:50.705
Hi.

01:11:52.609 --> 01:11:53.841
Hi.

01:12:00.317 --> 01:12:01.916
I'm sorry.

01:12:04.988 --> 01:12:07.922
I thought I was in control.
I wasn't.

01:12:08.992 --> 01:12:10.892
It's hard to explain.

01:12:10.894 --> 01:12:12.660
I tried them on.

01:12:14.731 --> 01:12:16.364
- You did?
- Mm-hmm.

01:12:16.366 --> 01:12:17.865
Jack had a pair.

01:12:18.735 --> 01:12:20.601
And?

01:12:20.603 --> 01:12:23.438
I don't know. I wore them for,
like, ten seconds.

01:12:25.875 --> 01:12:29.110
I didn't buy them for myself.
They were a gift.

01:12:29.112 --> 01:12:30.878
I don't care where
you got them, Felix.

01:12:30.880 --> 01:12:34.816
I just... [SIGHS]

01:12:36.019 --> 01:12:37.685
Do you have sex with it?

01:12:37.687 --> 01:12:39.987
I have a conversation
with it, okay?

01:12:39.989 --> 01:12:41.689
It's like a figure.

01:12:41.691 --> 01:12:43.758
This hologram, okay?

01:12:43.760 --> 01:12:45.793
And I... I can talk to her, okay?

01:12:45.795 --> 01:12:47.662
I can trust her, because...

01:12:47.664 --> 01:12:49.364
But you can't trust me?
Is that where we're at?

01:12:49.366 --> 01:12:51.766
No, no, no, of course.
Of course, I do.

01:12:51.768 --> 01:12:53.835
No, it's...

01:12:55.405 --> 01:12:57.138
It's easier.

01:12:59.843 --> 01:13:02.009
- It's difficult to explain.
- Felix.

01:13:05.382 --> 01:13:10.651
I choose every single day
to be married to you.

01:13:10.653 --> 01:13:13.454
And I'm going
to be honest with you.

01:13:13.456 --> 01:13:16.023
I don't always want to be.

01:13:16.025 --> 01:13:17.892
It's not easy.

01:13:19.129 --> 01:13:21.429
But it is my choice.

01:13:21.431 --> 01:13:25.066
This thing,
I'm sure that it listens,

01:13:25.068 --> 01:13:28.770
and it is supportive
and agreeable,

01:13:28.772 --> 01:13:31.439
but it is not real.

01:13:31.441 --> 01:13:36.077
This, right here, this is real.

01:13:40.917 --> 01:13:42.183
Okay.

01:13:45.722 --> 01:13:47.054
I'll work harder.

01:13:48.691 --> 01:13:50.091
I will.

01:13:51.995 --> 01:13:53.528
I want you.

01:13:58.768 --> 01:14:00.468
I'll be better.

01:14:02.806 --> 01:14:04.038
Okay?

01:14:05.041 --> 01:14:07.175
[INHALES DEEPLY AND SIGHS]

01:14:47.884 --> 01:14:49.917
- [ANNE] Hello!
- [GRACE] You smell like an airplane.

01:14:49.919 --> 01:14:51.786
You need to...
Oh, my parents are here.

01:14:51.788 --> 01:14:53.521
- [FELIX] Hey, honey.
- [GRACE] Hold on one second.

01:14:53.523 --> 01:14:55.022
Hello, guys.

01:14:55.024 --> 01:14:56.891
Hi, Mom.

01:14:56.893 --> 01:14:58.159
[OVERLAPPED CHATTER]

01:14:58.161 --> 01:14:59.760
Oh, hello!

01:14:59.762 --> 01:15:00.928
Mom, look who I have for you.

01:15:00.930 --> 01:15:02.864
[ANNE] Oh! Eve! Oh, my gosh!

01:15:02.866 --> 01:15:05.533
- Felix, you remember Eve.
- Hey.

01:15:11.074 --> 01:15:12.507
Oh, Eve.

01:15:12.509 --> 01:15:13.941
Are you okay?

01:15:13.943 --> 01:15:15.176
She just came back.

01:15:15.178 --> 01:15:17.245
[MUFFLED VOICES]

01:15:19.048 --> 01:15:20.982
She just came back
from college...

01:15:20.984 --> 01:15:23.184
[MUFFLED AUDIO]

01:15:26.189 --> 01:15:28.089
- Okay, I love you.
- I will text you about tomorrow.

01:15:28.091 --> 01:15:29.790
Yes, don't forget.

01:15:29.792 --> 01:15:31.259
- [EVE] Have fun.
- [GRACE] Okay. I love you.

01:15:31.261 --> 01:15:32.927
[EVE] See you.

01:15:32.929 --> 01:15:34.161
Bye-bye.

01:15:36.799 --> 01:15:38.266
[WHISPERING] Oh, God.

01:15:42.939 --> 01:15:44.205
[CHUCKLING]

01:15:44.207 --> 01:15:46.240
I think it is beautiful in here.

01:15:46.242 --> 01:15:48.175
You two have done a lovely job.

01:15:48.177 --> 01:15:49.877
Well, thank you.

01:15:49.879 --> 01:15:51.546
I am just grateful
that Ben hasn't exploded.

01:15:51.548 --> 01:15:53.014
I have no idea
what she's talking about.

01:15:53.016 --> 01:15:54.949
I love furniture shopping.

01:15:54.951 --> 01:15:57.051
You should have seen him when
we tried to buy a bookshelf.

01:15:57.053 --> 01:15:58.920
I thought he was going to
have an aneurysm.

01:15:58.922 --> 01:16:00.821
[LAUGHS]

01:16:00.823 --> 01:16:03.257
You know who is the worst
when it comes to furniture?

01:16:03.259 --> 01:16:05.326
- Your father.
- Really?

01:16:05.328 --> 01:16:10.131
Do you know that dresser
that was in your old room?

01:16:10.133 --> 01:16:12.033
Do you ever wonder
why it just tilts like that?

01:16:12.035 --> 01:16:13.968
- Oh, my God. Why?
- Your father...

01:16:13.970 --> 01:16:15.236
So we bought it flat-pack.

01:16:15.238 --> 01:16:16.938
He put it together.

01:16:16.940 --> 01:16:18.272
He got so...

01:16:18.274 --> 01:16:20.908
[VOICES MUFFLED]
frustrated, so infuriated...

01:16:22.245 --> 01:16:23.945
[GRACE] Oh, my God!

01:16:23.947 --> 01:16:26.180
[INDISTINCT MUFFLED CHATTER]

01:16:28.117 --> 01:16:29.350
Well done, Dad.

01:16:29.352 --> 01:16:30.952
[GRACE LAUGHS]

01:16:33.089 --> 01:16:34.355
Dad?

01:16:36.159 --> 01:16:37.592
Oh, Jesus.

01:16:37.594 --> 01:16:39.126
I'm sorry,
I must have zoned out.

01:16:39.128 --> 01:16:41.195
- You okay?
- Mm-hmm.

01:16:41.197 --> 01:16:43.230
Do you guys want
to stay afterwards

01:16:43.232 --> 01:16:46.000
and, like, watch a movie
or something?

01:16:46.002 --> 01:16:47.134
Yeah.

01:16:47.136 --> 01:16:48.903
- Great.
- I would love it.

01:16:48.905 --> 01:16:50.605
- Sounds great.
- Mm, what should we watch?

01:16:59.649 --> 01:17:01.349
[ANNE] You coming up?

01:17:03.686 --> 01:17:07.221
No. I'm going to call
Graciella, return a few emails.

01:17:07.223 --> 01:17:09.156
It's pretty late.

01:17:09.158 --> 01:17:11.292
I know. I'll be up soon.

01:17:11.294 --> 01:17:12.994
Okay.

01:17:14.631 --> 01:17:16.163
I love you.

01:17:20.103 --> 01:17:21.769
And I love you.
